He was a priest and is unmarried.
He also knows siddha medicine, astrology and yoga.
Being from Nanganallur, Chennai, he bought an acre of land there 15 years ago, and was living alone.
He was growing herbal plants all around the house.
In this scenario, a young woman Lavanya, from Besant nagar, Chennai, visited last Saturday and stayed with Govindaraj.
Govindaraj was performing pooja yesterday evening in the pooja room of the house.
Suddenly a mysterious object exploded with thunderous noise.
In this incident the body of Govindaraj caught fire.
He ran out of the house shouting.
Lavanya who came out upon hearing the noise, was shocked to see the scorched body of Govindaraj.
Govindaraj who sustained severe burns, died on the spot.
On hearing this information, Mappedu police rushed to the spot and sent the body of the deceased to Thiruvallur Government hospital for postmortem.
Lavanya luckily escaped, as she was in a nearby room when the mysterious object exploded.
It is not known if the mysterious object that exploded in the pooja room was a bomb.
What was the object that exploded in the pooja room?
It is not known if it is a bomb.
Forensic expert Nalina and officers led by Deputy Superintendent of Police Harini collected the evidence at the scene, which was then sent for analysis.
The mysterious object that exploded in the pooja room will only be known after the results are received.
There were also blood stains in the pooja room.
Police suspect that there would have been no chance of bleeding during the fire.
Based on the post mortem report of Govindaraj, the police have planned to conduct a further inquiry.
In relation to this incident, the lady who was staying with him is also being investigated.
