“If I do it, people also will come forward to do this!” says Ram Singh regarding this initiative, “People were fed up with the hardships of purchasing large amounts of vegetables, traffic jams and environmental pollution.
With so many people complaining about this, it does not seem that they thought of an alternative way, or realised that the solution lies with them.
The proper solution to this is, only if I do what I believe, people will be ready to follow.
So my wife and I walk 10 kms once a week to purchase vegetables.
Since this has continued for six months, we are now used to it.
"Now I am mentally very satisfied” he says.
